Dr. Silence drew a typewritten paper from his pocket.

â€œI can satisfy your curiosity to some extent,â€ he said, running
his eye over the sheets, and then replacing them in his coat; â€œfor
by my secretaryâ€™s investigations I have been able to check certain
information obtained in the hypnotic trance by a â€˜sensitiveâ€™ who helps
me in such cases. The former occupant who haunted you appears to have
